The Bosch H4 conversion kit is not DOT approved for street use for a
reason; the same reason people flash you. The beam shape is not
flattened at the top sufficiently to keep the light, even when on low
beam, from shining into oncoming drivers' eyes. A recipe for a head-on
collision. Yes, they are bright, but no brighter than the street legal
Hella conversion available here:

http://tinyurl.com/ywznru which comes with the bulb, making it about
four bucks cheaper.

Be courteous, be safe, be legal.
